<h1>About me</h1>
<p>I am not a unicorn-influencer-digital-ninja-artist: my job is to be a designer, quite simply. I therefore strive to always keep a critical eye on my profession, its methods and the goals it serves.</p>
<p>My design approach is always thought out in the context in which it takes place, in order to design interfaces and solutions for (and with) the user, based on dialogue, pedagogy, curiosity and empathy.</p>
<p>In short, in the midst of design systems, designing accessible interfaces, prototyping and meeting real people, I let my curiosity be nourished every day, with the very simple desire to constantly continue to learn new things.</p>

